          <li><strong>Monitored Preachers:</strong> Enslaved preachers allowed only under surveillance for ‚Äúsafe‚Äù messages.</li>
          <li><strong>Outcome:</strong> A theology of control‚Äîfaith became both a cage <em>and</em> the language of future rebellion.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Christianity as Social Discipline</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Selective Scripture:</strong> ‚ÄúCurse of Ham‚Äù (Gen 9) and ‚ÄúSlaves obey your masters‚Äù (Eph 6) naturalized hierarchy.</li>
          <li><strong>Missionary Catechisms:</strong> Charles Colcock Jones‚Äôs ‚Äúproper‚Äù slave Christianity centered on obedience over deliverance.</li>
          <li><strong>Supervised Worship:</strong> Plantation services under white oversight; enslaved preachers vetted for loyalty.</li>
          <li><strong>Purpose:</strong> Legitimize slavery as divine plan; suppress solidarity and rebellion.</li>
        </ul>
